The paper focuses on the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for document image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The authors also discuss the use of data augmentation and architecture design, which are common topics in deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper analyzes the learned features of the CNNs, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL) or information retrieval (cs.IR) depending on the specific features being analyzed.
